Mazor Robotics Drops Most Since March 2009 as Loss Widens

-- B y   G w e n   A c k e r m a n
-- 
2011-08-14T13:36:23Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-14/mazor-robotics-drops-after-saying-second-quarter-loss-widened.html
Mazor Robotics Ltd. (MZOR)  dropped the most
in two-and-a-half years after the maker of surgical robots said
the second-quarter loss almost tripled to 10.5 million shekels
($3 million).  The shares fell 16 percent, the biggest decline since March
2009, to 4.939 shekels at the 4:30 p.m. close in  Tel Aviv .  The Caesarea, Israel-based company said revenue declined to
1.96 million shekels from 4.19 million shekels in the year-
earlier period, when it had a loss of 3.7 million shekels.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Gwen Ackerman in Jerusalem at 
 gackerman@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Maedler at 
 cmaedler@bloomberg.net  